  "prompt": "How many First Ladies have refused to live in the White House?",
  "response": "Throughout history, a few First Ladies have chosen not to live in the White House for various reasons. The most noted example is Anna Harrison, the wife of President William Henry Harrison. She never moved into the White House because President Harrison passed away just a month after his inauguration. Another instance is Martha Washington, who lived in the presidential manor in Philadelphia, as the White House was not yet completed when George Washington was president. Therefore, technically Anna Harrison is the only First Lady to have outright refused to live in the White House when it was available, but circumstances around her decision were unique due to her husband's sudden death.",
